<ACTION>
ACTION:

 Proposed rule; correction and extension of public comment period.






</ACTION>
<SUMMARY>
SUMMARY:

 EPA is extending the public comment period for 30 days, from January 21, 1994 to February 22, 1994, and correcting a
proposed test rule published in the 

Federal Register

 of November 22, 1993 (58 FR 61654) requiring manufacturers and processors of five chemicals (acetophenone, phenol,
N,N-dimethylaniline, ethyl acetate, and 2,6-dimethylphenol) to conduct testing for certain chemical fate, health
and environmental effects. 


</SUMMARY>
